SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1023
By Hatcher
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Dustin Matthew Pedigo
of Rockwood.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the untimely passing of Dustin Matthew Pedigo of Rockwood; and
WHEREAS, Dustin Pedigo was a compassionate gentleman who worked assiduously to
improve the quality of life for his family, his friends, and his community in numerous capacities;
and
WHEREAS, born on June 26, 1990, Mr. Pedigo was a graduate of Heritage High School
and was pursuing a bachelor's degree in sociology at East Tennessee State University; and
WHEREAS, Dustin Pedigo served the Tennessee Department of Correction with
acumen and alacrity, performing with uncommon devotion in securing the safety of his
community; he was deeply passionate about his work in the corrections field, and he
endeavored to reduce recidivism and provide trauma-informed support to those in his care; and
WHEREAS, he was also deeply devoted to his family and always endeavored to remain
true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Pedigo will be sadly missed yet fondly remembered by his wife, Bethany
"Jade" Bowman-Pedigo; his parents, Ken and Karen Pedigo; his brother, Brandon Pedigo; his
sister, Kerri Pedigo; his grandmother, Grace Moore; his niece, Nadine; and a host of aunts,
uncles, cousins, and in-laws; and
WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his grandparents, Linda Robison, Clay
Teffeteller, Oscar Melvin Pedigo, and Sam Moore; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Pedigo was a warm and kindhearted soul who greatly impacted the
lives of those who were blessed to know him; he leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity
SJR1023
015945
- 1 -

and probity in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in
all his chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the bountiful life of this exceptional human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Dustin Matthew Pedigo,
reflecting fondly upon his impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the
examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Pedigo.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
